  "original_title": "\u0dc3\u0dd2\u0db4\u0dd9\u0da7\u0dca\u0d9a\u0ddd \u0db4\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dc0\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dca\u0dc4\u0dbd\u0dca \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0daf\u0dda\u0dc1 \u0dc3\u0db8\u0dcf\u0d9c\u0db8\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dbd\u0da7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Ceypetco filling stations to foreign companies",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Power and Energy Minister Kanchana Wijesekera today (Jan. 26) said that a cabinet paper will be tabled tomorrow (27) to hand over petrol stations owned by the Ceylon Petroleum Corporation (Ceypetco) to foreign companies.",
        "The Minister said that he hopes to give opportunity to companies in fuel producing countries and that those companies should not be burdened with foreign exchange by borrowing fuel from their parent companies for a period of 6 months or a year.",
        "Minister Wijesekera said that if the 1190 filling stations owned by the Ceylon Petroleum Corporation could be provided to those companies at least 200 each, the fuel problem could be resolved, adding that Indian Oil had requested for the establishment of 50 more filling stations or new filling stations."
      ],
